<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n26091d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26091d">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26091d"> 91(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> speak in &frac12; tones</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> On the following day (continues Caesarius) &ldquo;she came again and since she replied Dominus when she was saluted, the maiden added: &lsquo;Good Sister Gertrude, why come you at such a time and what seek you with us?&rsquo; Then she replied: &lsquo;I come here to make satisfaction. Because I willingly whispered with thee in the choir, <mark>speaking in half tones</mark>, therefore am I ordered to make satisfaction in that place where it befell me to sin. And unless thou beware of the same vice, dying thou shalt suffer the same penance.&rsquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>&rdquo; <small> Eileen Edna Power, <a name="MLEN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MLEN"><cite title="source">Medieval English Nunneries</cite></a> (1922) 28n3f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
